<br>
With that said, pick up group are dangerous.  Flat out deadly in most cases.  The only time I go LFG is on my rogue on the odd times he's just playing around.  Most of the folks in my guild are busy leveling alts and are now of a level where they can join me if they wish to.  If I dont want to group, which is often because I can easily use downtime to do laundry, wash dishes, etc. I solo in whatever zone I find some good XP and little competition.<br>
<br>
I recommend a good guild with people of a like level, and soloing and XP grinding while you can.   <p><img src=http://24.26.194.142/sevepic.gif></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=conalglassbones>Conal Glassbones</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/22/03 6:35:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26204.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: very bad day of EQ</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Whenever I complain about not being about to get a group some idiot always pipes up and says I should go solo.<br>
