You have to realize that the problems you are having are not your fault but are problems in the games design.<br>
I am experiencing something similar. I hardly ever get groups unless it is with friends, and the timing for that doesn't work out real often, so I am forced to solo. <br>
But, since making lvl 61 and Sony's briliiant idea to make everything that is not in PoP turn light blue or green to me, my options for soloing are very limited. I have a few flags, but really the only place I can do any good and that is reasonably safe is PoS Loroks, and unfortunately there are only about 4 of them and they are always camped (and I have seen some people do some pretty shitty things to acquire/keep that camp, of these mobs that wander all over). So yeah, I have become a bit jaded on the game myself of late. I might take a break, or at least only raid with my guild until such time as Sony decides to undo this level range thing they did to lvl 61+'s. But I don't take it personally. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=corinia>Corinia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/22/03 10:56:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26204.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.burleehost.com/moyguild/avitars/sorceress.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards</span><hr size=1> I have always grouped.  I hate soloing.  I am just now learning to quad kite at level 52 and I've had jboots since level 38 or so.  I feel that I am a very good wizard in grouping situations and have been very lucky.  First of all, my family plays so they are usually on at the same time as I.  My husband (ranger) and brother (paladin) and I will generally group together but if they're not available, I have never had a problem finding a group.  I think it depends on your mindset.<br>
<br>
What are you looking for exactly?  Just to be in a group?  Experience, equipment, friendliness - all of these factor in.  I don't always group where I want to fight because sometimes I go to join friends.  I like to be around people.  Sometimes they come to where I want to fight.<br>
<br>
The first person mentioned not being able to get into a guild.  What kind of guild are you looking for?  I've found that most guilds are political and unless you're well liked you don't get much.  The guild I am in is a family guild.  We don't consider ourself uber.  We don't believe in raiding all the time.  We do believe hunting together.  We believe in giving things to each other and helping others in the world of Norrath as well.  So there is almost always someone I can group with from the guild.<br>
<br>
If there is absolutely no one available or the guild is off fighting (we have a lot of higher levels who can go places I don't go yet) somewhere else I can generally find a group somewhere.  I've gone to the LOY zones and just asked for a camp check and then told to people asking if they'd like to take a level 52 wizzy in and made a few friends that way.  As I've worked on my epic, I've made friends with people needing to slay the same mobs and can check with them if they need help.  I never go LFG.  I just ask people (in tells directly) if they need someone or find a pickup group at zoneline (and then move them to a safer place if that's a rough zoneline with trains).<br>
<br>
I also suggest what someone else suggested.  Put the group together yourself.  I've gone to zones and when I couldn't actually get INTO a group I would ooc group needs such and such classes and then as I got tells I'd have them meet me somewhere and that would work to get a group together.<br>
<br>
Good luck with finding a group.  It's not as hard as you may think. <p>Renia - wizardess of Cazic-Thule<br>
Baroness of MoY who aspires to greatness (and may attain it one day).</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nulland>Nulland</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/22/03 11:50:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26204.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards</span><hr size=1> I feel your pain.  I'm flagged up to BoT/HoH, but it hasn't done me a bit of good.  I can LFG for hours, while the same three types of classes (melee/healer/slower) get nabbed almost immediately.  So much min/max'ing goes on now, that unless you are well known and have some of the right friends, it just seems near impossible to get *consistent* grouped xp.  After you get passed up so many times for a group, it gets very difficult to not take it personally and develop some angst.<br>
<br>
I literally spent months being helpless, but since last week, I returned to what I knew... soloing.  Part of the reason I abandoned soloing in the first place was all the hype surrounding xp in PoV when grouped (especially since all the solo spots in PoV are so contested).  However, let me assure you, that even though the xp might be better in an IC group in PoV, the xp I get solo is much more consistent, efficient, and dependable.  In less than one week, I have gone from zero xp in 61 to zero xp in 64... in a tier one zone at that.  For me, the only person I can depend on is myself.  It gets boring and lonely, but it is a means to an end... the end being 65, which greatly improves your marketability (or so it seems).<br>
