say hi to those on your friends list?  What does it take to answer their call for help?  Friendships are born that way.  Don't make excuses to be anti-social.  It is not at all healthy. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=328193"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/hibashirasakai/HibashiraNewHalfSize.txt"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nulland>Nulland</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/22/03 7:28:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26204.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards</span><hr size=1> Oh I agree with everything you're saying, Hibashira.  It's still difficult, though... especially since a seemingly large portion of my server's population seem more interested in asserting their virtual superiority than forming friendships.  It almost seems as though people feel they have enough friends and are unwilling to develop new ones. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yyen>yyen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/22/03 7:41:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26204.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards</span><hr size=1> Whether you get a group or not is 75 percent class, 20 percent luck, and p